children.name: Text
children.characters:
The value is set by the Auto Layout “Spacing between items” property of a specific layer. This may seem like a weird way to move a dot along a line, but it’s the only way you can move a nested object within a component’s instance

To set the value, 
Select the “🌈 Progress Bar: component
Go to the layers panel and find the layer “Value >> Edit AL Spacing ...” 
Inspect the Auto Layout properties on the right, and adjust the “Spacing between items” property (]I[ icon) up and down in value.

children.name: Text
children.characters: The main use case for the Progress Bar in Pendo is to show progress when uploading an item:

children.name: Text
children.characters:
Choose the variant you need from the sidebar
 
The color of progress circles can be customized, however we recommend using the colours that are defined in the variants.

Size is also customizable, but there are also recommended sizes that we already use in the product

children.name: Text
children.characters: To modify the value of the circle double click into the coloured section and select a handle and draag to move. Or enter a specific value, you can change this in the properties panel

children.name: Text Description
children.characters: The progress bar component typically communicates the loading state progress, it can also be used for metrics, such as within tables.

children.name: Value >> Edit AL Spacing to Change Start Position

To update the or value of a progress bar navigate to the layer called "Value >> Edit AL Spacing to Change Start Position" Go to the Auto Layout property on the right and adjust up (or down) the "Spacing between items" value (it's the one with the ]|[ icon)
